                <h4>What is the voting age population of Berwick, Louisiana?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Berwick, Louisiana, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 3,269.  The voting age population is 42.6% male and 57.4% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berwick, Louisiana residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 12.2% of
                        the residents of Berwick are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Berwick, Louisiana?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Berwick are 83.4% White, 11.6% Black, 2.0% American Indian, 1.9% Other and 1.1% Two or more races. Additionally, 4.2% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berwick, Louisiana residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Berwick, 25.3% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 22.1%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    15.2% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Berwick.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berwick, Louisiana residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 50.3% of
                    Berwick residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Berwick, Louisiana residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    77.5% of
                    Berwick residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 13.7%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 4.3%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Berwick, Louisiana residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Berwick residents aged 5 and older, 5.6% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                3.9% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.7% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Berwick, Louisiana?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Berwick is 6.6%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berwick, Louisiana residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Berwick, 11.9% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
